Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.65,0:00:12.95,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima-kun is still down by 5 cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.35,0:00:15.45,Chiha-internal,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,He can't catch up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.77,0:00:17.59,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,That early mistake is making a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.59,0:00:21.20,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,He stabilized midway through the \Ngame and made some good plays,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.83,0:00:24.60,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,but his luck is still terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.84,0:00:27.85,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,The last five cards \Nhave been on my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.68,0:00:32.15,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Should I focus on defending \Nthe seven cards on my side
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.89,0:00:34.52,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,instead of attacking the \Ntwo on the opponent's side?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.26,0:00:42.51,ghost,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(800,1)}Living Ghost
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.87,0:00:42.73,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need you, Dr. Harada.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.98,0:00:47.73,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,When in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.73,0:00:50.01,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,As the years pass...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.06,0:00:50.01,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Go lower right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.80,0:00:51.78,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:00:54.80,Chiha-main,Ichi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.80,0:00:57.04,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.85,0:00:59.00,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Two wins for Fujisaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.00,0:00:59.88,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.88,0:01:00.71,Chiha-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,One more win!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.71,0:01:01.87,Chiha-main,D,0000,0000,0000,,One more win for the championship!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.17,0:01:03.28,Chiha-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.28,0:01:06.37,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa's down 0 to 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.04,0:01:08.58,Chiha-internal,D,0000,0000,0000,,They're strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.30,0:01:11.20,Chiha-internal,D,0000,0000,0000,,That makes it a five-peat for Fujisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.98,0:01:13.65,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending a card.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.04,0:01:16.60,Chiha-card-TS,,0000,0000,0000,,the cresting waves almost look like clouds in the skies
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.36,0:01:18.47,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,A multi-syllable card?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.74,0:01:21.94,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,"My only thought as I" was already read,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.94,0:01:23.47,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,so this is now a two-syllable card.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.88,0:01:26.61,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,You won't be able to surprise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.02,0:01:28.26,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sticking to my usual playing style.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.01,0:01:30.39,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,This is painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.39,0:01:32.71,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,It would be most gratifying \Nif Mizusawa was able
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.71,0:01:35.49,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,to secure a single win from \Nthe dominating Fujisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.97,0:01:36.99,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Three wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.38,0:01:41.26,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,We're getting three wins, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.62,0:01:54.09,Chiha-title2,A,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1800)}Chihaya Furu
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.10,0:02:57.11,Chiha-ep-title-verse,EpTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(950,800)}Episode 19
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.10,0:02:57.11,Chiha-ep-title-poem-wide,EpTitle,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(950,800)}I do not \Nknow \Nwhere \Nthis love \Nwill take \Nme
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.90,0:03:02.80,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,We're getting three wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.31,0:03:08.17,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,Don't bother bluffing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.57,0:03:10.36,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible you won't even get a single win.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.02,0:03:12.00,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.70,0:03:14.16,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima went there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.82,0:03:17.00,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Three wins, when we're cornered like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:20.13,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,He's always let his actions speak for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.13,0:03:22.11,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,He's careful and has a lot of pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.11,0:03:24.51,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,He's always thinking about \Nwhat happens when he loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.35,0:03:27.68,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Even when he volunteered \Nto play their captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.46,0:03:30.43,Chiha-flashback,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll play their captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.83,0:03:33.09,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.24,0:03:35.70,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,is trying to change!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.96,0:03:38.09,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.49,0:03:42.58,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.10,0:03:44.78,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,He keeps wasting time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.52,0:03:47.99,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I have six cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:50.00,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,My opponent has two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:52.77,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,There are plenty of dead cards left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.75,0:03:56.40,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"After many," "The emotions," \N"The hazed early dawn mist,"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:04:00.95,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"The sight," "May it," "My life," \N"When I," "Nothing," "Silent,"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.95,0:04:04.68,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"Gust," "I feel," "As my," \N"Since I," "For you I head."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.74,0:04:07.67,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,My opponent won't make \Nany memorization errors.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.57,0:04:10.55,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,He's aware of the changing unique syllables.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.91,0:04:14.19,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.63,0:04:21.04,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.69,0:04:21.57,prettyboy,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(225,1)}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.61,0:04:24.63,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only coach I've ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.20,0:04:26.45,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,When in trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.16,0:04:28.29,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,go lower right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:28.70,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the cresting waves almost look like clouds in the skies
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.01,0:04:29.95,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:32.21,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!  Come on!  Come on!  Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.21,0:04:34.42,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Read it!  Read it!  Read it!  Read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:36.26,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Give it!  Give it!  Give it!  Give it!  Give it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.26,0:04:37.84,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!  Come on!  Come on!  Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.09,0:04:46.18,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,My only thought as the boat \Ntakes me out to sea is that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.03,0:04:47.97,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,It was read...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.46,0:04:50.31,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,It was read.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.67,0:04:52.10,Chiha-internal,All,0000,0000,0000,,It was read!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.30,0:04:58.23,Chiha-flashback,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima sent the multi-syllable \Ncard to give himself a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.11,0:05:02.63,Chiha-flashback,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,The Fujisaki captain is \Nvery good at covering,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.63,0:05:04.32,Chiha-flashback,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,so he has a habit of covering \Nmulti-syllable cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:06.40,Chiha-flashback,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Even when it's not necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.99,0:05:08.12,Chiha-flashback,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,He's open to attack then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.96,0:05:11.83,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,He's using my data!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.83,0:05:14.08,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,He's only down three now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.57,0:05:26.97,Chiha-internal,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?  What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.36,0:05:31.78,Chiha-internal,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,He was on a roll...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.43,0:05:34.77,Chiha-internal,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,It is hard to decide what card \Nto send towards the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.77,0:05:36.59,Chiha-internal,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,but this isn't the time to stress over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.66,0:05:51.53,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending a card.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:55.37,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,which shines over Mount Mikasa
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.20,0:06:05.00,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,the cresting waves almost look \Nlike clouds in the skies
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.49,0:06:08.55,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,The storm blasts autumn...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:10.43,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}to set the Tatsuta River ablaze
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.55,0:06:10.43,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}which shines over Mount Mikasa
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.12,0:06:14.26,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,Eromu went for the "The sky \Nmay" on his own side?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.92,0:06:16.01,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,A fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.01,0:06:17.10,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Even better!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.86,0:06:19.10,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,Double fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.43,0:06:20.91,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Eromu-senpai committed a double fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.91,0:06:22.01,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,First time I've seen that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.01,0:06:24.71,Chiha-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,He rarely commits faults, \Nlet alone a double...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.84,0:06:29.96,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,I needed to refresh my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.93,0:06:36.81,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.52,0:06:40.31,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,He knew exactly which card \Nhe was going to send.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.88,0:06:42.75,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,He pretended to take a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.28,0:06:47.20,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,so he could reinforce what the \Nfield would look like in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:51.72,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first fault he's made.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.78,0:06:54.72,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I know you have to be tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.47,0:06:57.29,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Five matches lasting over nine hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.03,0:07:00.39,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,And also, the Tokyo regional champions,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.96,0:07:02.03,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Hokuo,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.53,0:07:04.23,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,would have made you work for your win.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.33,0:07:08.21,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I guarantee it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.47,0:07:12.28,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,With that double fault,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.28,0:07:15.49,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,the Prez removes one card from \Nhis side and sends another...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.68,0:07:15.49,Chiha-card-TS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(417.1)}the plum blossoms still smell the same
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:18.92,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,It's 3 to 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.36,0:07:20.34,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,He's caught up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.66,0:07:23.54,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending "In order for."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.99,0:07:30.05,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,Amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.64,0:07:34.60,Chiha-internal,Kuri,0000,0000,0000,,The battle in the middle is getting fierce.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.97,0:07:40.85,Chiha-internal,Kuri,0000,0000,0000,,It's 5 to 1...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.85,0:07:43.06,Chiha-internal,Kuri,0000,0000,0000,,The Mizusawa player \Nonly has one card left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.47,0:07:44.55,Chiha-internal,Kuri,0000,0000,0000,,When did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.86,0:07:52.02,Chiha-internal,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Yamashiro-san panicked \Nand committed a fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.13,0:07:55.37,Chiha-internal,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Neither of them are using \Nany sort of strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.33,0:07:59.37,Chiha-internal,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,This is a battle of sound and reflex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.09,0:08:02.27,Chiha-internal,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,The difference between \Nthem is barely perceivable,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.47,0:08:05.52,Chiha-internal,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,but it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.07,0:08:08.88,Chiha-internal,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Enough of a difference for \None to emerge victorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.21,0:08:14.78,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there.  Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.54,0:08:16.89,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.99,0:08:20.89,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,The Urayasu room in the Omi \NJingu Learning Center.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.89,0:08:28.26,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,to set the Tatsuta River ablaze
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.63,0:08:26.52,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Right next to the reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.63,0:08:31.15,Chiha-internal,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,In the seat that assures victory!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.07,0:08:38.83,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,Rion!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.98,0:09:08.41,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.66,0:09:15.15,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.50,0:09:17.36,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:18.90,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,Try not to disturb her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.90,0:09:19.58,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:21.16,asleep,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(458,1)}She's asleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.70,0:09:22.76,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:33.17,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,No call to announce \NMizusawa's first win...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.57,0:09:42.38,Chiha-main,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending "No more."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.84,0:09:45.63,Chiha-internal,Mana,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Kanata?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.63,0:09:48.19,Chiha-internal,Mana,0000,0000,0000,,He's clawing his way back \Nfrom the early deficit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.81,0:09:50.08,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.08,0:09:53.44,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,As the game drags on, his guesses \Nhave been more accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.86,0:09:57.02,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,It takes experience to be able \Nto feel the flow of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.12,0:10:00.26,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I've been playing karuta since I was five.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.72,0:10:02.95,Chiha-internal,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I've been playing longer \Nthan anyone else here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.04,0:10:08.48,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to becoming Queen,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.09,0:10:11.78,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,it's much harder for us to \Nbecome best in Japan together!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.11,0:10:15.83,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.11,0:10:25.64,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,and by no fault of mine
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.99,0:10:28.85,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Said world grants no escape
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.86,0:10:31.17,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Eromu-senpai got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.17,0:10:32.53,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,He's so fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:40.07,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,He's quick when it comes to cards \Nthat are now one-syllable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.99,0:10:48.01,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I can't lose here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.70,0:10:50.67,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.71,0:10:56.31,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have plenty of chances to \Ntry to become Master and Queen,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.92,0:11:00.59,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm moving "Like a."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.98,0:11:05.63,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,but we only get to play as a team
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.63,0:11:07.35,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,during our three years in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.12,0:11:09.73,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,The sky may hold...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.51,0:11:13.31,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!  He defended it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.40,0:11:18.75,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm moving my card.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.29,0:11:23.95,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,It's down to luck-of-the-draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.29,0:11:26.70,Chiha-internal,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,In both games...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.39,0:11:28.70,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:31.96,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them are in \Nluck-of-the draw situations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:36.11,Chiha-card-TS,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know where this love will take me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.86,0:11:38.50,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know where this love will take me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.38,0:11:45.30,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,Mizusawa synchronized their cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:50.56,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,There's no guarantee that we'll make \Nit back to the finals next year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.30,0:11:55.16,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,We'll probably never get \Nanother chance like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.05,0:11:58.11,Chiha-card-TS,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know where this love will take me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.79,0:12:04.80,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,The famous Sone no Yoshitada poem...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.64,0:12:10.16,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,Like a boatsman adrift at the mouth of the Yura, I do not know where this love will take me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.97,0:12:09.52,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Of all cards, this is the \None the Prez gets...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.16,0:12:17.67,Chiha-card-TS,Caption,0000,0000,0000,,No more can we hear the sounds of the waterfall, but its legacy continues to spread
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.84,0:12:13.24,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,The opposing captain has "No more."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.85,0:12:17.67,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,I like these poems much more than \Nthe ones that are more technical.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.08,0:12:25.92,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,The mouth of the Yura is \Nwhere river meets ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.26,0:12:29.74,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,There, love lost its oar in the waters,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.30,0:12:32.09,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,left with no idea where it will go...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.31,0:12:35.42,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Chihaya,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.09,0:12:38.27,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,wake up...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.46,0:12:41.17,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to watch
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.48,0:12:45.35,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,my fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.73,0:12:49.58,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,It's over if "Like a" is read.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.24,0:12:53.03,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect Mizusawa to \Nsynchronize their cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.13,0:12:55.19,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,Surely they didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.99,0:12:57.24,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,It must be coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.91,0:13:00.00,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't expecting a luck-of-the-draw,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.00,0:13:01.92,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,but Emuro-kun has strong luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.67,0:13:05.93,Chiha-internal,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,This match will end 4 to 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.72,0:13:08.01,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,This was no coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.61,0:13:10.43,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,They were setting this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.12,0:13:12.43,Chiha-flashback,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending "In order for."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.13,0:13:14.69,Chiha-flashback,Pork,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending "No more."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:17.14,Chiha-flashback,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm moving "Like a."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.90,0:13:20.76,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,They understand how \Nto play team matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.30,0:13:22.16,Chiha-internal,Retro,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.72,0:13:24.66,Chiha-internal,Retro,0000,0000,0000,,Two of their games are \Ndown to luck-of-the-draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.92,0:13:27.91,Chiha-internal,Retro,0000,0000,0000,,They synced their cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.34,0:13:29.95,Chiha-internal,Retro,0000,0000,0000,,They pulled it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.30,0:13:39.46,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,It's 50/50.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.87,0:13:42.02,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,We have a 50% chance of winning...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.02,0:13:45.88,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,A 50% chance of our cards being read.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.62,0:13:47.47,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.88,0:13:49.34,Chiha-internal,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.92,0:13:53.00,Chiha-internal,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima have his card read \Nin a luck-of-the-draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.89,0:14:00.48,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,How long has it been since \NEromu's last luck-of-the-draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.15,0:14:04.99,Chiha-internal,Ichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did Eromu relax because he was \Nup against a Class B player?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.99,0:14:06.38,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's still okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.38,0:14:07.99,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Eromu-senpai's card will be read.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.78,0:14:12.12,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,I can visualize my "No more" being read.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.42,0:14:18.29,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,Sealing Fujisaki's five-peat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.99,0:14:26.05,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think my card will be read,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.18,0:14:29.54,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,but I doubt I can take the last card
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.54,0:14:31.86,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,from a player who's \Nsuch a good defender.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.03,0:14:40.34,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Remember to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.88,0:14:42.44,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I can't give up yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.96,0:14:45.94,Chiha-card-TS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1460,1)}I do not know where this love will take me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.84,0:14:45.94,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"Like" is a one-syllable card now,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.23,0:14:47.98,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,but "Nothing" hasn't been read,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.26,0:14:51.22,Chiha-card-TS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1017,1)}but its legacy continues to spread
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.54,0:14:50.30,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,so he can't take "No more" \Non the first syllable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:52.95,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Do I attack?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:55.69,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,It won't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.52,0:14:57.79,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,But if I don't attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.79,0:15:05.99,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,which shines over Mount Mikasa
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:13.02,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,For you, I head out to the \Nfields to pick spring greens
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.55,0:15:17.08,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Nishida also went on the attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.09,0:15:21.77,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,They intend to attack the opponent's \Nside in a luck-of-the-draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.18,0:15:25.32,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Since I could not hide...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.18,0:15:28.18,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Still nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:30.30,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,His guard is so low.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.83,0:15:32.45,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,There's no opening to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.74,0:15:36.20,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.53,0:15:38.00,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.53,0:15:42.38,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,It's too much!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.38,0:15:43.77,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm too scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.15,0:15:45.96,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.64,0:15:50.84,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:52.70,Chiha-internal,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,Mashima-senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.66,0:15:59.39,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,The one card I need won't be read.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.08,0:16:01.57,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,It never is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.55,0:16:04.47,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how my life will go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.43,0:16:08.78,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Is everything I do futile?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.43,0:16:12.14,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Six more dead cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.65,0:16:18.62,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,"After many," "May it," "My life," \N"Nothing," "Silent," "Gust"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.04,0:16:22.08,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Is it futile to keep remembering these?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.28,0:16:34.31,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Still...  God...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.82,0:16:36.99,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.06,0:16:41.77,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if my card is never \Nread in a luck-of-the-draw again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.35,0:16:44.27,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,So please...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.77,0:16:46.79,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Just today...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.27,0:16:49.27,Chiha-internal,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,This one time...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.46,0:16:54.54,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,Just this once...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.78,0:16:57.83,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,Like a boatsman adrift...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.56,0:17:11.31,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,W-We did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.31,0:17:12.74,Chiha-main,Tsu,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!  We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.74,0:17:13.76,Chiha-main,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.76,0:17:15.78,Chiha-main,Sumi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!  We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.18,0:17:16.07,Chiha-overlap,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,Quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.29,0:17:21.12,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,The match isn't over
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.22,0:17:24.73,Chiha-main,Kana,0000,0000,0000,,until the second verse has been read.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.87,0:17:35.42,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,...adrift at the mouth of the Yura,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.78,0:17:44.71,Chiha-poem,N,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know where \Nthis love will take me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.65,0:17:52.80,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.33,0:17:55.69,Chiha-main,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,You've got tatami marks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.47,0:18:13.56,Chiha-main,Mura,0000,0000,0000,,The winner of the team \Nchampionship is Mizusawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.56,0:18:15.66,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,by a score of 3 to 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.66,0:18:17.24,Chiha-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.05,0:18:19.74,Chiha-main,All,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.69,0:18:22.94,Chiha-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,We lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.94,0:18:24.04,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,Second place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.06,0:18:26.59,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,We came in second.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.82,0:18:31.85,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,This loss is my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.58,0:18:34.39,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,If I were the god of karuta,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.94,0:18:37.74,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,I would have sided with Mizusawa \Nfor their valiant display.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.14,0:18:42.55,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault for building a \Nteam solely based on strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.15,0:18:47.07,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,I looked down on my opponent \Nfor spending an entire year
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.07,0:18:48.38,Chiha-internal,,0000,0000,0000,,kicking around Class B.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.22,0:18:51.31,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,That was my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.07,0:18:55.43,Chiha-internal,Ero,0000,0000,0000,,That guy's on his way up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.60,0:18:59.98,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,Ri-Rion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.98,0:19:02.21,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,You're not supposed to show emotion!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.21,0:19:03.45,Chiha-internal,Mako,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.31,0:19:07.12,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,Rion, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.81,0:19:11.52,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,None of our players are capable \Nof defeating Ayase-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.22,0:19:14.27,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault that you couldn't win,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.14,0:19:19.63,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,but you need to realize that you \Nlost despite having the advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.75,0:19:24.51,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,Learn some humility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.53,0:19:29.54,Chiha-main,Saku,0000,0000,0000,,It's on you to make sure that we don't \Nlose a single match next summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.07,0:19:33.66,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,The ceremony will be on the \Nfirst floor in 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.66,0:19:35.55,Chiha-main,A,0000,0000,0000,,Please prepare as necessary \Nand proceed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.72,0:19:38.31,Chiha-main,B,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.31,0:19:41.53,Chiha-main,C,0000,0000,0000,,We had some excellent matches this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.53,0:19:44.28,Chiha-main,D,0000,0000,0000,,So Mizusawa is our champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.20,0:19:52.34,Chiha-flashback,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,If you become the best player in Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.34,0:19:54.23,Chiha-flashback,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be the best in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.59,0:19:58.33,Chiha-flashback,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in team tournaments.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.03,0:20:01.22,Chiha-flashback,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,I'm focused on winning the \Nindividual tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.37,0:20:07.27,Chiha-main,Miya,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's head downstairs, Ayase-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.69,0:20:27.24,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,D-Did you watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.59,0:20:28.16,Chiha-main,Ara,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.67,0:20:29.65,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Were you watching?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.05,0:20:37.76,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,My team is the best in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:41.63,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,I became the best in Japan \Nwithout becoming Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.47,0:20:46.72,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,It's because we were playing together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.73,0:20:49.97,Chiha-main,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that you're not \Ninterested in teams!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.95,0:20:55.25,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,And then there's the \N"Impassionate gods" card!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.25,0:20:57.94,Chiha-flashback,Chi,0000,0000,0000,,Wataya-kun said that the card \Nhas the same name as me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.15,0:21:00.39,Chiha-flashback,Tai,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us will \Nwin together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.40,0:21:10.21,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.12,0:21:17.03,Chiha-main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
